title: Pharmacy worker tests positive for coronavirus as another primary school is forced to shut
description: It's believed the worker from a National Pharmacies store in Adelaide contracted the virus through a link to a cluster of infections at the Adelaide Airport.
content:
Updated 
April 02, 2020 11:47:24
An Adelaide pharmacy worker has tested positive for COVID-19, forcing 15 employees into self-isolation, as another primary school is closed due to the positive test of a staff member.
